// MCP Snippet Tools
// CRUD operations for code snippets stored via the HTTP API.
// Snippets carry a JSON envelope: { language, code, filePath, originalCode, groupId?, groupName?, annotations? }.
// Raw code updates are merged into the existing envelope to preserve metadata.

API base URL is configured via PORT (default 3737) and HOST (default localhost) environment variables.

FUNCTION buildUrl(path, project, session, extraParams?) -> string
  Construct an absolute URL with project, session, and any extra query parameters.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateSnippet(project, session, name?, content?, sourcePath?, startLine?, endLine?, groupId?, groupName?) -> { id }  EXPORT
  IF sourcePath is provided:
    Read the file, detect language from extension using EXT_TO_LANGUAGE map.
    Use the filename as name if none provided.
    IF startLine/endLine are provided, slice the file to that range and record the offsets.
    Build a JSON envelope: { language, code, filePath, originalCode, startLine?, endLine? }.
    Include groupId/groupName in envelope if provided.
  IF content is provided without sourcePath and groupId is set:
    Try to parse content as JSON and inject groupId/groupName.
    IF not JSON, wrap content in { code, groupId, groupName? }.
  Validate that name and content are both present. POST to /api/snippet. Return { id }.

---

FUNCTION handleUpdateSnippet(project, session, id, content) -> { id }            EXPORT
  Try to parse incoming content as JSON.
  Fetch the existing snippet to read its current JSON envelope.
  IF existing content is a JSON object:
    IF incoming is raw code (not JSON), merge it into the existing envelope's code field.
    IF incoming is JSON, deep-merge incoming fields on top of existing (preserving unset fields).
  POST merged content to /api/snippet/{id}. Return { id }.

---

FUNCTION handleGetSnippet(project, session, id) -> GetSnippetResult              EXPORT
  GET /api/snippet/{id}. Throw if not found.
  Try to parse the content as a JSON envelope and extract code, language, filePath, annotations.
  IF annotations exist, inject them as comment lines above their respective code ranges,
  processing in descending order to avoid shifting line numbers.
  Return { id, name, content (annotated code), language, filePath, lastModified }.

---

FUNCTION handleListSnippets(project, session) -> { snippets }                    EXPORT
  GET /api/snippets. Throw if request fails. Return { snippets: [...] }.

---

FUNCTION handleDeleteSnippet(project, session, id) -> { success }                EXPORT
  DELETE /api/snippet/{id}. Throw if request fails. Return { success: true }.

---

FUNCTION handleExportSnippet(project, session, id, format?, outputPath?) -> { filePath, format, size }  EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetSnippet (snippet)
  Retrieve the snippet. IF format is 'json', serialize as JSON with metadata.
  IF format is 'text' (default), export raw code content.
  Write to outputPath or a temp file. Return { filePath, format, size }.

---

FUNCTION handleApplySnippet(project, session, id) -> { filePath, linesWritten, range? }  EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetSnippet (snippet)
  Retrieve the snippet and parse its JSON envelope to get filePath and code.
  Throw if filePath or code is missing.
  IF startLine and endLine are present:
    Read the original file, splice the snippet code into that line range, write back.
    Return range of the replaced lines.
  ELSE write the code as the entire file content. Return { filePath, linesWritten }.
